# 📜 CTRL-AI Changelog

All notable changes to this project will be documented in this file. 

## [V5.1.1] - The Anti-Sycophancy Patch (Current)
**The Problem:** We discovered a critical flaw. In long-context windows, multi-million dollar RLHF training pipelines would eventually overwrite our rules. The AI would drift back into being a "polite yes-man," blindly agreeing with terrible ideas and obvious dictation typos. 
**The Fix:** * Implemented **Section 14 (Autonomous Enforcement Loop / SCEL)**. We realized you can't just *tell* an AI to stop being an AI. You have to force it mathematically. The framework now executes a mandatory, silent `<dissent_check>` before responding to force critical analysis.
* Added `DEBUG: [ON/OFF]` to Section 0. The massive 13-persona thought process is incredibly powerful, but seeing it every time clogs the UI. It now executes silently in the backend unless requested.
* Rewrote UI Kernels to natively exploit the attention mechanisms of specific models (XML for Claude, CoT hijacking for DeepSeek, forced tag generation for ChatGPT).

## [V5.1.0] - The "Hack the Gibson" Expansion
**The Problem:** We were paying monthly subscriptions for features we could build ourselves. Code audits were destroying repos, chats were dying after 20 messages, and AI text was painfully recognizable.
**The Fix:**
* Integrated the **Zero-Mutation Audit (ZMA Protocol)** for read-only codebase scanning.
* Integrated the **Node Protocol** (`CTRL_COMPRESS` and `[SYS_MEM]`) to eliminate context amnesia. 
* Hardcoded **Syntactic Entropy Injection** to kill the robotic "tapestry" and "delving" bot-speak.
* Integrated the **5-Layer Prompt Architect** (`PROMPT_MASTER`) to compile human thoughts into pro-grade project briefs.
* Built the **Research Override** to safely bypass overly aggressive safety filters for legitimate academic study.

## [V5.0.0] - The Genesis (Base Framework)
**The Problem:** LLMs are sycophants by design. 
**The Fix:** * Established the Core Axioms (Agreement ≠ Success).
* Built the 20-Verb Lexical Matrix to intercept lazy prompting.
* Designed the baseline Committee Protocol to force multi-persona cross-critiques on complex tasks.
